    AmplNLReader.eval
    NLPModels.ghjvprod — Function.

    Compute the vector of dot products (g, Hj*v) where Hj is the Hessian of the j-th constraint at x.

    NLPModels.ghjvprod! — Function.

    Compute the vector of dot products (g, Hj*v) in place where Hj is the Hessian of the j-th constraint at x.

    NLPModels.grad — Function.

    Evaluate the gradient of the objective function at x.

    NLPModels.grad! — Function.

    Evaluate the gradient of the objective function at x in place.

    NLPModels.hess — Function.

    Evaluate the Lagrangian Hessian at (x,y) as a sparse matrix. Only the lower triangle is returned.

    NLPModels.hess_coord — Function.

    Evaluate the Lagrangian Hessian at (x,y) in sparse coordinate format. Only the lower triangle is returned.

    NLPModels.hprod — Function.

    Evaluate the product of the Lagrangian Hessian at (x,y) with the vector v.

    NLPModels.hprod! — Function.

    Evaluate the product of the Lagrangian Hessian at (x,y) with the vector v in place.

    AmplNLReader.include
    NLPModels.jac — Function.

    Evaluate the constraints Jacobian at x as a sparse matrix.

    NLPModels.jac_coord — Function.

    Evaluate the constraints Jacobian at x in sparse coordinate format.

    NLPModels.jprod — Function.

    Evaluate the Jacobian-vector product at x. Warning: Currently building the Jacobian for this.

    NLPModels.jprod! — Function.

    Evaluate the Jacobian-vector product at x in place. Warning: Currently building the Jacobian for this.

    NLPModels.jth_con — Function.

    Evaluate the j-th constraint at x.

    NLPModels.jth_congrad — Function.

    Evaluate the j-th constraint gradient at x.

    NLPModels.jth_congrad! — Function.

    Evaluate the j-th constraint gradient at x in place.

    NLPModels.jth_hprod — Function.

    Evaluate the product of the j-th constraint Hessian at x with the vector v. The objective Hessian is used if j=0.

    NLPModels.jth_hprod! — Function.

    Evaluate the product of the j-th constraint Hessian at x with the vector v in place. The objective Hessian is used if j=0.

    NLPModels.jth_sparse_congrad — Function.

    Evaluate the j-th constraint sparse gradient at x.

    NLPModels.jtprod — Function.

    Evaluate the transposed-Jacobian-vector product at x. Warning: Currently building the Jacobian for this.

    NLPModels.jtprod! — Function.

    Evaluate the transposed-Jacobian-vector product at x in place. Warning: Currently building the Jacobian for this.

    NLPModels.lagscale — Function.

    Set the scaling factor σ in the Lagrangian: L(x,y) = f(x) + σ ∑ yi ci(x).
